  "prompt": "How do you block someone on Quora?",
  "response": "Blocking someone on Quora is a straightforward process. Here are the steps you can follow to block someone:\n\n1. **Go to Their Profile**: Navigate to the profile of the person you want to block. You can do this by clicking on their name or profile picture wherever it appears on Quora.\n\n2. **Click on Options**: On their profile page, you'll see three vertical dots (the options menu) usually located near the top right corner of the page.\n\n3. **Select \"Block\"**: Click on the three dots to open the menu, then select \"Block\" from the dropdown list.\n\n4. **Confirm**: Confirm that you want to block the person. Once you confirm, the person will be blocked, meaning they won't be able to see your content or interact with you.\n\nBlocking someone on Quora will prevent them from commenting on your answers or posts, sending you messages, or following you. They will also be unable to see your activity on the platform, and you won't see theirs.",
